Properties.Description:
The nature of the relationship between two or more animals.

Ex:
- Put-together Cattle
- Breeding Stock
- Crossbreeding
- Sire 
- Dam
- Half sib
- Full sib 
- Calf
- Freemartin
- Crossbreeding
- Terminal Cross
- Backcross
- Linecross
- Random mating

where:

Put-together Cattle
Cattle that have been assembled by an order buyer from small lots.

Breeding Stock
Sexually mature male and female livestock that are retained to produce offspring.

Crossbreeding
The mating of animals of different breeds. For example, breeding a Hereford cow with an Angus bull.

Sire 
Male parent of calf

Dam
Female parent of calf

Half sib
Half brothers or half sisters

Full sib 
Full brothers or full sister

Calf

Freemartin
Heifer calf born as a twin to a bull calf, usually infertile

Crossbreeding
Mating animals from different breeds to utilize hybrid vigor (heterosis), breed

Terminal Cross
Breeding a female with a bull whose major characteristics focus on weight production. All offspring are sold.

Backcross
The mating of a two-breed crossbred offspring back to one of its parental breeds. Example: A Hereford-Angus cross cow bred back to an Angus bull.

Linecross
Offspring produced by crossing two or more inbred lines.

Random mating
A system of mating where every female (cow and/or heifer) has an equal or random chance of being assigned to any bull used for breeding in a particular breeding season. Random mating is required for accurate progeny tests.
